com.knitting.jamacoi
Class Result_Tree

java.lang.Object
  com.knitting.jamacoi.Result_Tree

public class Result_Tree
extends java.lang.Object

This class provides the mechanism of saving f-values returned by a search of an instance of the Table_of_F_Tables class. The returned f-values are the ones that "match" the regression data's degrees-of-freedom for:

1) the sum-of-squared errors explained by the independent variables.
2) the sum-of-squared errors NOT explained by the independent variables.

In addition to saving the "matching" f-values, this class:

1) provides the method to organize and list the returned f-value matches.
2) provides the method to compare each returned f-value to the regression's f-value result.

Method Detail

put_data

public void put_data(java.lang.String s,
                     F_Table_Cell c)
This method adds elements to the instance of the TreeMap in the Result_Tree class. Each element in the TreeMap contains:

1) the name of the F_Table_Cell instance. The name is the significance level from which the F_Table_Cell was extracted.
2) a F_Table_Cell instance.

Parameters:
s - is the name (or significance level) of the F_Table_Cell
c - is an F_Table_Cell instance that "matched" the regression's pair of degrees-of-freedom values.
